exactInputSingleWithServiceFee((address,.details: Takes a fee on the input token, by taking a cut from the `amountIn`, of the size of the fee amount, before doing the swap.      This means that the developer, when quoting the swap, should calculate the fee amount and decrease the `amountIn` by that amount.This swap has only one hop.Emits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipient.

params.serviceFee: The details of the service fee(s).

params.serviceFee: The details of the service fee(s).

exactOutputSingleWithServiceFee((address.details: Takes a fee on the output token, by increasing the `amountOut` by the fee amount.      This means that the developer, when quoting the swap, should calculate the fee amount and increase the `amountOut` by that amount.Emits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipient.This swap has only one hop.

params.serviceFee: The details of the service fee(s).

exactOutputWithServiceFee((address,uint1.details: Takes a fee on the output token, by increasing the `amountOut` by the fee amount.      This means that the developer, when quoting the swap, should calculate the fee amount and increase the `amountOut` by that amount.Emits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipient.This swap has multiple hops.

params.serviceFee: The details of the service fee(s).
